<%= l_ui_title_bar(title: "Examples") %>

<p class="l-ui-utility--mt-md">
  Two examples, each demonstrating a distinct capability of the gem.
</p>

<h2 class="l-ui-utility--mt-xl"><%= link_to "Users", users_path %></h2>
<p class="l-ui-utility--mt-md">
  Restricted actions via <code>only: %i[index edit update destroy]</code> - no show, no create. The <code>posts_count</code> column links to posts scoped to that user, demonstrating nested resources via <code>scope "users/:user_id"</code> and a <code>PostResource.scope</code> override.
</p>

<h2 class="l-ui-utility--mt-xl"><%= link_to "Posts", posts_path %></h2>
<p class="l-ui-utility--mt-md">
  The baseline: <code>layered_resources :posts</code> plus a <code>PostResource</code> declaring columns, fields, and search fields. You get index, show, new, edit, and destroy - with search, sort, pagination, and forms styled out of the box.
</p>
